IP Addressing ( Layer 3 of the OSI; Internet layer of the TCP/IP )
	- 32 bit Binary Number (Identifier)
	- Reported in Dotted Decimal Notation:  e.g. 192.168.10.100 (4 octets--4 sets of 8 binary bits)
	- 2 portions
		+ NetworkID: logical grouping
		+ HostID: unique identifier within that group
	-e.g Street Address
		123 Sesame St. 
			- 123 House Number
			- Sesame St. Street Name
			- each house on the street must have a unique number.
-32 bit number: 4.3 Billion
